Nike Unisex Footwear Trends: A Web Scraping Data Analysis¶

########################### SCRAPING ALL UNISEX SALE SHOES #############################

#necessary imports
from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.service import Service
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys
import time


from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.service import Service
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys
import time


driver = webdriver.Chrome()

driver.implicitly_wait(10)
driver.set_script_timeout(120)
driver.set_page_load_timeout(10)

#browsing the nike site
driver.get('https://www.nike.com/')


#Clicking on men category
men = driver.find_element(By.LINK_TEXT, 'Men')
men.click()
time.sleep(3)


#select all shoes
shoes = driver.find_element(By.PARTIAL_LINK_TEXT, 'Shoes')
shoes.click()
time.sleep(3)


# select dropdown
sort_by_button = driver.find_element(By.CLASS_NAME, 'dropdown.anchored--right.css-gkljb0')
sort_by_button.click()
time.sleep(5)

# sort by price - low to high
sort = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, '//button[text()="Price: Low-High"]')
sort.click()
time.sleep(3)

#click on sales drop down
sales_dropdown = driver.find_element(By.CLASS_NAME, 'trigger-content__label')
sales_dropdown.click()
time.sleep(3)                              
  
# click on sales
sale = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, '//span[contains(text(), "Sale")]')
sale.click()
time.sleep(3)

# click on gender dropdown
gender = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, "//div[contains(@class, 'trigger-content__label') and text()='Gender']")
gender.click()
time.sleep(3)

# click on men filter
filters = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, '//span[contains(text(), "Men")]')
filters.click()
time.sleep(3)

# click on unisex filter
filters2 = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, '//span[contains(text(), "Unisex")]')
filters2.click()
time.sleep(3)


# scroll till the end of the page 

initial_height = driver.execute_script("return document.body.scrollHeight")
while True:
    # Scroll down to bottom
    driver.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")
    # Wait for new content to load
    time.sleep(3)
    new_height = driver.execute_script("return document.body.scrollHeight")
    if new_height == initial_height:
        break  
    initial_height = new_height  

    
# save sale products to local nike html    
with open("nike.html" , "w" , encoding ='utf-8') as file:
       file.write(driver.page_source)
       
time.sleep(3)        
driver.quit()

# Parsing theorugh the saved sale unisex shoes page
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import time
import os


# reading saved html file and parsing
with open("nike.html" , "r" , encoding ='utf-8') as file:
       html_content = file.read()

soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser')
print(soup.prettify())

   function onMouseFocus(e) {
    window.requestAnimationFrame(function addMouseFocus() {
      var body = document.querySelector('body');
      body.classList.add('mouse-focus');
      body.classList.remove('keyboard-focus');
    });
  }
  function onKeyboardFocus(e) {
    window.requestAnimationFrame(function addKeyboardFocus() {
      var body = document.querySelector('body');
      body.classList.add('keyboard-focus');
      body.classList.remove('mouse-focus');
    });
  }
  window.addEventListener('mousedown', onMouseFocus);
  window.addEventListener('keydown', onKeyboardFocus);

   <script>
    try {
    (function () {
        const checkClass = 'at-pw-promo-checked';
        const promoMessage = 'Extra 20% Off w/ SPRING';
        var skuJsonUrl = 'https://storage.googleapis.com/site_css_js/nike/nike_032024_updated.json';

        const buildDesktopPromo = (message) => {
            const div = document.createElement('div');
            div.classList.add('at-pw-promo');
            div.innerHTML = message;
            return div;
        };

        const buildStyle = () => {
            const style = document.createElement('style');
            style.innerHTML = `
                .at-pw-promo { font: var(--podium-cds-typography-body1-strong); color: rgb(0, 125, 72); display: block; padding-top: 10px; }
       
                .at-pw-promo.at-pw-promo-hide {
                    display: none;
                }

                .at-pw-perc-disc { padding-left: 5px; padding-top: 0; }

                .product-card__price > div.product-price__perc.css-1rz91t { display: none; }
            `;
            return style;
        }

        const processProductNodes = (nodes, skuList, promoMessage) => {

            nodes.forEach(node => {
                node.classList.add(checkClass);
                const linkNode = node.querySelector('figure > a');
                if (linkNode) {
                    const linkParts = linkNode.href.split('/');
                    const stylecolor = linkParts[linkParts.length - 1];
                    const priceNode = node.querySelector('.product-card__price');
                    const oldNodes = priceNode.querySelectorAll('.at-pw-promo');
                    const isPromo = skuList.includes(stylecolor);

                    const priceWrapper = priceNode.querySelector('.product-price__wrapper');

                    setTimeout(() => {
                        let compressedNodeDiscountNode = priceWrapper.querySelector('.at-pw-perc-disc');
                        if (compressedNodeDiscountNode) {
                            compressedNodeDiscountNode.remove();
                        }
                        const discountNode = priceNode.querySelector('.product-price__perc');
                        if (discountNode) {
                            compressedNodeDiscountNode = discountNode.cloneNode(true);
                            compressedNodeDiscountNode.classList.add('at-pw-perc-disc');
                            priceWrapper.appendChild(compressedNodeDiscountNode);
                        }
                    }, 1); //next tick

                    if (isPromo) {
                        node.querySelector('.product-card__body').classList.add('product-card_at-styled')
                        if (oldNodes && oldNodes.length > 0) {
                            oldNodes.forEach(oldNode => {
                                oldNode.classList.remove('at-pw-promo-hide');
                            });

                        } else {
                            priceNode.appendChild(buildDesktopPromo(promoMessage));
                        }
                    } else {
                        if (oldNodes && oldNodes.length > 0) {
                            node.querySelector('.product-card__body').classList.remove('product-card_at-styled')
                            oldNodes.forEach(oldNode => {
                                oldNode.classList.add('at-pw-promo-hide');
                            });
                        }
                    }
                }
            });
        };

        const elementReady = (selector, root) => {
            const _root = root || document.body;
            let result;
            return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
                result = _root.querySelectorAll(selector);
                if (result && result.length > 0) {
                    resolve(result);
                    return
                }
                new MutationObserver((mutationRecords, observer) => {
                    result = _root.querySelectorAll(selector);
                    if (result && result.length > 0) {
                        resolve(result);
                        observer.disconnect();
                    }
                }).observe(_root, {
                    childList: true,
                    subtree: true
                });
            });
        };

        const observeForColorTiles = (root, skuList, promoMessage) => {
            elementReady(`.product-card__colorways-thumbs .colorway:not(.${checkClass}) img[src*="https"]`, root).then(colorwayImages => {

                colorwayImages.forEach(function (colorwayImage) {
                    const colorway = colorwayImage.closest('.colorway');
                    colorway.classList.add(checkClass);

                    const productCard = colorway.closest('.product-card');
                    colorway.addEventListener('mouseover', () => {
                        setTimeout(() => { processProductNodes([productCard], skuList, promoMessage); }, 1);
                    });
                });
                observeForColorTiles(root, skuList, promoMessage);
            });
        };

        const observeForProductCards = (root, skuList, promoMessage) => {
            elementReady(`[data-testid="product-card"]:not(.${checkClass})`, root).then(products => {
                processProductNodes(products, skuList, promoMessage);
                observeForProductCards(root, skuList, promoMessage);
            });
        };

        const getSkus = (url) => {
            return fetch(url).then(response => {
                return response.json().then(json => {
                    return json.productToSelect;
                });
            });
        };

        getSkus(skuJsonUrl).then(skuList => {
            elementReady('#skip-to-products').then(roots => {
                roots[0].parentNode.appendChild(buildStyle());
                observeForProductCards(roots[0], skuList, promoMessage);
                observeForColorTiles(roots[0], skuList, promoMessage)
            })
        });
    })();
}
catch (e) {
    if (window.newrelic) {
        window.newrelic.addPageAction('Bluecore Campaign Error', {
            campaign: 'Product Wall Promo DT',
            error: e.toString(),
        });
    }
    console.log(e);
}

   <script>
    try {
    (function () {
        const checkClass = 'at-pw-promo-checked';
        const promoMessage = 'Extra 20% Off w/ SPRING';
        var skuJsonUrl = 'https://storage.googleapis.com/site_css_js/nike/nike_032024_updated.json';

        const buildDesktopPromo = (message) => {
            const div = document.createElement('div');
            div.classList.add('at-pw-promo');
            div.innerHTML = message;
            return div;
        };

        const buildStyle = () => {
            const style = document.createElement('style');
            style.innerHTML = `
                .at-pw-promo { font: var(--podium-cds-typography-body1-strong); color: rgb(0, 125, 72); display: block; padding-top: 10px; }
       
                .at-pw-promo.at-pw-promo-hide {
                    display: none;
                }

                .at-pw-perc-disc { padding-left: 5px; padding-top: 0; }

                .product-card__price > div.product-price__perc.css-1rz91t { display: none; }
            `;
            return style;
        }

        const processProductNodes = (nodes, skuList, promoMessage) => {

            nodes.forEach(node => {
                node.classList.add(checkClass);
                const linkNode = node.querySelector('figure > a');
                if (linkNode) {
                    const linkParts = linkNode.href.split('/');
                    const stylecolor = linkParts[linkParts.length - 1];
                    const priceNode = node.querySelector('.product-card__price');
                    const oldNodes = priceNode.querySelectorAll('.at-pw-promo');
                    const isPromo = skuList.includes(stylecolor);

                    const priceWrapper = priceNode.querySelector('.product-price__wrapper');

                    setTimeout(() => {
                        let compressedNodeDiscountNode = priceWrapper.querySelector('.at-pw-perc-disc');
                        if (compressedNodeDiscountNode) {
                            compressedNodeDiscountNode.remove();
                        }
                        const discountNode = priceNode.querySelector('.product-price__perc');
                        if (discountNode) {
                            compressedNodeDiscountNode = discountNode.cloneNode(true);
                            compressedNodeDiscountNode.classList.add('at-pw-perc-disc');
                            priceWrapper.appendChild(compressedNodeDiscountNode);
                        }
                    }, 1); //next tick

                    if (isPromo) {
                        node.querySelector('.product-card__body').classList.add('product-card_at-styled')
                        if (oldNodes && oldNodes.length > 0) {
                            oldNodes.forEach(oldNode => {
                                oldNode.classList.remove('at-pw-promo-hide');
                            });

                        } else {
                            priceNode.appendChild(buildDesktopPromo(promoMessage));
                        }
                    } else {
                        if (oldNodes && oldNodes.length > 0) {
                            node.querySelector('.product-card__body').classList.remove('product-card_at-styled')
                            oldNodes.forEach(oldNode => {
                                oldNode.classList.add('at-pw-promo-hide');
                            });
                        }
                    }
                }
            });
        };

        const elementReady = (selector, root) => {
            const _root = root || document.body;
            let result;
            return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
                result = _root.querySelectorAll(selector);
                if (result && result.length > 0) {
                    resolve(result);
                    return
                }
                new MutationObserver((mutationRecords, observer) => {
                    result = _root.querySelectorAll(selector);
                    if (result && result.length > 0) {
                        resolve(result);
                        observer.disconnect();
                    }
                }).observe(_root, {
                    childList: true,
                    subtree: true
                });
            });
        };

        const observeForColorTiles = (root, skuList, promoMessage) => {
            elementReady(`.product-card__colorways-thumbs .colorway:not(.${checkClass}) img[src*="https"]`, root).then(colorwayImages => {

                colorwayImages.forEach(function (colorwayImage) {
                    const colorway = colorwayImage.closest('.colorway');
                    colorway.classList.add(checkClass);

                    const productCard = colorway.closest('.product-card');
                    colorway.addEventListener('mouseover', () => {
                        setTimeout(() => { processProductNodes([productCard], skuList, promoMessage); }, 1);
                    });
                });
                observeForColorTiles(root, skuList, promoMessage);
            });
        };

        const observeForProductCards = (root, skuList, promoMessage) => {
            elementReady(`[data-testid="product-card"]:not(.${checkClass})`, root).then(products => {
                processProductNodes(products, skuList, promoMessage);
                observeForProductCards(root, skuList, promoMessage);
            });
        };

        const getSkus = (url) => {
            return fetch(url).then(response => {
                return response.json().then(json => {
                    return json.productToSelect;
                });
            });
        };

        getSkus(skuJsonUrl).then(skuList => {
            elementReady('#skip-to-products').then(roots => {
                roots[0].parentNode.appendChild(buildStyle());
                observeForProductCards(roots[0], skuList, promoMessage);
                observeForColorTiles(roots[0], skuList, promoMessage)
            })
        });
    })();
}
catch (e) {
    if (window.newrelic) {
        window.newrelic.addPageAction('Bluecore Campaign Error', {
            campaign: 'Product Wall Promo DT',
            error: e.toString(),
        });
    }
    console.log(e);
}
   </script>

# Retriving the sale shoes - list of links 

from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import os
import shutil

# list of BeautifulSoup 'a' tag objects with 'href' attributes
links = soup.find_all('a', class_='product-card__link-overlay')

# define Directory to save html files
directory = 'nike_links3'

# if the directory exists, and if it does  delete it
if os.path.exists(directory):
    shutil.rmtree(directory)

# Create the new directory 
os.makedirs(directory, exist_ok=True)

cnt = 0
# Loop through each HTML content to get the href to a new product html file
for i, link in enumerate(links, start=1):
    href = link.get('href')
    try:
        # request to get the HTML content of the page
        response = requests.get(href)
     
        if response.status_code == 200:
            filename = os.path.join(directory, f'page_{i}.html')
            with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
                f.write(response.text)
            print(f"Saved HTML content of {href} to {filename}")
            cnt = cnt +1 # to check the number of links saved
        else:
            print("Failed to retrieve " , href)
    except requests.RequestException as e:
        print("Request failed: ", e)

print("Saved html pages to the directory: ", directory)

#################### OBTANING VARIOUS ATTRIBUTES FOR ALL SALE SHOES #####################

import os
import re
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

path = 'nike_links3'  # saved html files path

# List to hold dictionaries of product info
nike_products_list = []  

# Looping through each file in the directory
for file_name in os.listdir(path):
    if file_name.endswith(".html"):
        filepath = os.path.join(path, file_name)
        with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as file:
            html_content = file.read()

        soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser')

        # Dictionary to store product info
        product_info = {}

        #  product title
        title_element = soup.select_one('h1')
        title = title_element.text.strip() if title_element else "NULL"
        print("Product title is:", title)
        product_info['title'] = title

        # print category
        category_element = soup.select_one('h2')
        category = category_element.text.strip() if category_element else "NULL"
        print("Footwear Style Category is:", category)
        product_info['category'] = category

        #  sale price
        sale_price_element = soup.find(attrs={"data-test": "product-price-reduced"})
        sale_price = sale_price_element.get_text().strip() if sale_price_element else "NULL"
        print("Product Sale Price is:", sale_price)
        product_info['sale_price'] = sale_price

        # original price
        original_price_element = soup.find(attrs={"data-test": "product-price"})
        original_price = original_price_element.get_text().strip() if original_price_element else "NULL"
        org_price_match = re.search(r'\$\d+', original_price)
        org_price = org_price_match.group() if org_price_match else "NULL"
        print("Original Product price is:", org_price)
        product_info['original_price'] = org_price

        #  discount offer
        offer_element = soup.find(attrs={"data-testid": "OfferPercentage"})
        if offer_element:
            offer_perc = offer_element.get_text().strip()
            offer_perc_final = offer_perc.split()[-2] if offer_perc else "NULL"
            print("Discount Offer on the product is:", offer_perc_final)
        else:
            print("No discount offer available for this product.")
        product_info['discount_offer'] = offer_perc_final if offer_element else "NULL"

        # description
        desc_element = soup.select_one('.description-preview.body-2.css-1pbvugb > p')
        desc_final = desc_element.get_text(strip=True) if desc_element else "NULL"
        print("Description is:", desc_final)
        product_info['description'] = desc_final

        # product ID
        element = soup.select_one('.description-preview__style-color.ncss-li')
        style_id = element.text.strip()[-11:] if element else "NULL"
        print("The Product ID for the product is:", style_id)
        product_info['product_id'] = style_id

        #  number of reviews
        review_span = soup.select_one('h3.headline-4 > span')
        number_of_reviews = review_span.get_text(strip=True).split('(')[-1].strip(')') if review_span else "NULL"
        print("Number of reviews is:", number_of_reviews)
        product_info['number_of_reviews'] = number_of_reviews if review_span else "0"

        # rating
        rating_div = soup.find('div', class_='css-n209rx')
        rating = rating_div.get('aria-label') if rating_div else "NULL"
        print("Rating is:", rating)
        product_info['rating'] = rating

        # Add the product_info dictionary to the list
        nike_products_list.append(product_info)

        print("*****************************************************************************************************")

############ ALL SHOES COLLECTION CATEGORIES ###############


from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.service import Service
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys
import time


driver = webdriver.Chrome()

driver.implicitly_wait(10)
driver.set_script_timeout(120)
driver.set_page_load_timeout(10)

driver.get('https://www.nike.com/')


time.sleep(5)

#select shoes category - total 887 reuslts
men = driver.find_element(By.LINK_TEXT, 'Men')
men.click()
time.sleep(5)

# select shoes
shoes = driver.find_element(By.LINK_TEXT, 'Shoes')
shoes.click()
time.sleep(5)

# select collections dropdown
collections_button = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, '//div[@aria-label="Collections"]')
collections_button.click()
time.sleep(5)


from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import os
import shutil

# to get the list of elements in the collections category
soup = BeautifulSoup(driver.page_source, 'html.parser')
collections = soup.find_all('div', class_='Collapsible filter-group filter-group__open')
for collection in collections:
    
    print(collection.get_text())
    print("\n")

time.sleep(3)        
driver.quit()

In [7]:
import re

# using regex to filer, separate and create a list for all elements
for collection in collections:
    collections_text = collection.get_text()
  
#Removing the unwanted parts 
cleaned_text = re.sub(r"Collections\s*\(\d+\)|\+ More|- Less", "", collections_text)

# comma as delimiter before capital letters and number where there is no space
collections_set = re.sub(r"(?<=[a-z0-9])(?=[A-Z])", ",", cleaned_text)
collection_names = collections_set.split(',')
print(collections_set)
print(collection_names)

############## DEFINING DATABASE AND TABLE DETAILS ##############

import mysql.connector
import warnings

import requests
import json
import codecs
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

#ignore warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")



# Define the database and table details
SQL_DB = "nike"   
SQL_TABLE_NIKE = "products"
SQL_TABLE_NIKE_DEF = "(" + \
        "product_id VARCHAR(255) PRIMARY KEY," + \
        "title TEXT," + \
        "category TEXT," + \
        "sale_price VARCHAR(255)," + \
        "original_price VARCHAR(255)," + \
        "discount_offer VARCHAR(255)," + \
        "description TEXT," + \
        "number_of_reviews INT," + \
        "rating VARCHAR(255)" + \
        ")"

Create Database and Table

In [9]:
##################### CREATING THE DATABASE AND TABLE ##################

import mysql.connector
import requests


try:
    #connect to server
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()


    query = "CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS " + SQL_DB
    cursor.execute(query);

    conn.database = 'nike'
    
    query = "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE
    cursor.execute(query);
        
    query = "CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS " + SQL_DB + "." + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE_DEF + ";";
    cursor.execute(query);

    
    cursor.close()
    conn.close()

    print("Created NIKE Database and Products Table")
except IOError as e:
    print(e)

Created NIKE Database and Products Table

######################### INSERTING THE DATA INTO THE TABLE ###############

SQL_DB = "nike"   
SQL_TABLE_NIKE = "products"

try:
    #connect to server
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()
    cursor.execute('USE nike')

    # Prepare insert query
    insert_query = f"INSERT INTO " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " (product_id, title, category, sale_price, original_price, discount_offer, description, number_of_reviews, rating) \
     VALUES (%s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s);"
    
    row_count = 0
    for product in nike_products_list:
        row_count += 1
        user_data = (
            product.get("product_id"),
            product.get("title"),
            product.get("category"),
            product.get("sale_price"),
            product.get("original_price"),
            product.get("discount_offer"),
            product.get("description"),
            product.get("number_of_reviews"),
            product.get("rating")
        )
        cursor.execute(insert_query, user_data)
        conn.commit()
        
    print(f"{row_count} rows of data inserted successfully.")
    cursor.close()
    conn.close()

except mysql.connector.Error as e:
    print("MySQL error:", e)

191 rows of data inserted successfully.

#################### INSERTING THE COLLECTIONS TABLE TO THE DATABASE #################

import mysql.connector
import requests
import json

# Defining the database and table details
SQL_DB = "nike"
SQL_TABLE_NIKE = "collections"
SQL_TABLE_NIKE_DEF = "(" + \
        "name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL UNIQUE" + \
        ")"


try:
    #connecting to server
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()
    #cursor.execute('USE github')

    query = "CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS " + SQL_DB
    cursor.execute(query);

    conn.database = 'nike'
    
    query = "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE
    cursor.execute(query);
        
    query = "CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS " + SQL_DB + "." + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE_DEF + ";";
    cursor.execute(query);
    cursor.close()
    conn.close()

except IOError as e:
    print(e)

try:
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()
    cursor.execute('USE nike')

    insert_query = "INSERT INTO " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " ( name) VALUES ( %s);"
    

    row_count = 0

    for name in collection_names:
        try:
            cursor.execute(insert_query, (name,))
            conn.commit()  # Commiting after each insert
            row_count += 1
        except mysql.connector.Error as e:
            print(f"Error inserting {name}: {e}")

    print("Collections inserted successfully.")

    
    print(row_count, "rows of data inserted successfully.")

    cursor.close()
    conn.close()

except mysql.connector.Error as e:
    print("MySQL error:", e)

Collections inserted successfully.
17 rows of data inserted successfully.

Data Wrangling¶

Manipulating the data to make it usable for analysis

If a title contains a collection name, that name will be inserted into the 'collection' column. If not, 'others' will be used to signify that it doesn't match any of the known collections.

In [13]:
import mysql.connector

SQL_DB = "nike"   
SQL_TABLE_NIKE = "products"

try:
    #connect to server
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()
    cursor.execute('USE nike')

    #  if 'collection' column already exists then nochange and add it if it doesn't alter table
    cursor.execute("SELECT * FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS WHERE TABLE_SCHEMA = %s AND TABLE_NAME = 'products' AND COLUMN_NAME = 'collection'", (SQL_DB,))
    result = cursor.fetchone()
    if not result:
        query = "ALTER TABLE " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " ADD COLUMN collection VARCHAR(255)"
        cursor.execute(query);
        
     # Select all product titles from the table
    cursor.execute(f"SELECT product_id, title FROM products;")
    products = cursor.fetchall()
        

    # Checking for Collection name in the title
        
    # first update collection with 'others'
    for product_id, title in products:
        collection_name = 'others'
        title = title.strip()  
    
    # Check if any of the known collection names are in the title, if available then update collection column
        for collection in collection_names:
            if collection.lower() in title.lower():
                collection_name = collection
                break
            
            
        update_query = f"UPDATE products SET collection = %s WHERE product_id = %s;"
        cursor.execute(update_query, (collection_name, product_id))
        
       
    conn.commit()
    print("The 'collection' column is updated.")
except mysql.connector.Error as error:
        print("Failed to update records to nike db: ", error)

cursor.close()
conn.close()
print("MySQL connection is closed.")

The 'collection' column is updated.
MySQL connection is closed.

################### SCRAPING ALL UNISEX NIKE SHOES ( INCLUDES THE ONE ON SALE AND NON SALE BOTH) ############


from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.service import Service
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.common.keys import Keys

men.click()
time.sleep(5)


shoes = driver.find_element(By.LINK_TEXT, 'Shoes')
shoes.click()
time.sleep(5)


gender = driver.find_element(By.CLASS_NAME, 'trigger-content__label')
gender.click()
                              
                             
filters = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, '//span[contains(text(), "Men")]')
filters.click()
time.sleep(3)


filters2 = driver.find_element(By.XPATH, '//span[contains(text(), "Unisex")]')
filters2.click()
time.sleep(3)



# scroll till the end of the page 

initial_height = driver.execute_script("return document.body.scrollHeight")
while True:
    # Scroll down to bottom
    driver.execute_script("window.scrollTo(0, document.body.scrollHeight);")
    # Wait for new content to load
    time.sleep(3)
    new_height = driver.execute_script("return document.body.scrollHeight")
    if new_height == initial_height:
        break  
    initial_height = new_height  
    
    
# saving the non sale 
with open("nike_non_sale.html" , "w" , encoding ='utf-8') as file:
       file.write(driver.page_source)
       
time.sleep(3)  
driver.quit()

################ SCRAPING NO. OF COLORS AVAILABLE FOR ALL SHOES ###########

import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import time
import os

#read saved html file
with open("nike_non_sale.html" , "r" , encoding ='utf-8') as file:
       html_content = file.read()

soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser')
#print(soup.prettify())   

color = []
colors_elements = soup.select('.product-card__count-item')

# Extract the full text for each element and clean it up
for ele in colors_elements:
    color_text = ele.get_text().strip()
    color.append(color_text)  # Append the full text to the color list
color_numbers = [int(c.split()[0]) for c in color]
    
# Print the results
for colors in color_numbers:
    print(colors)

############### SAVING ALL NON SALE SHOE LINKS IN HTML FILE #######################


from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import requests
import os
import shutil

# 
links = soup.find_all('a', class_='product-card__link-overlay')


# new directory to save the non sale HTML files
directory = 'nike_links_nonsale3'

#  if the directory exists, and if it does, delete it
if os.path.exists(directory):
    shutil.rmtree(directory)


os.makedirs(directory, exist_ok=True)

cnt = 0

for i, link in enumerate(links, start=1):
    href = link.get('href')
    try:
        # request to get the HTML content 
        response = requests.get(href)
       
        if response.status_code == 200:
            filename = os.path.join(directory, f'page_{i}.html')
            with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
                f.write(response.text)
            print(f"Saved HTML content of {href} to {filename}")
            cnt = cnt +1
        else:
            print(f"Failed to retrieve {href}")
    except requests.RequestException as e:
        print(f"Request failed: {e}")

print(f"Saved {i} pages to the directory: {directory}")

############ OBTANING VARIOUS ATTRIBUTES FOR ALL NON SALE SHOES ###############

import os
import re
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

path = 'nike_links_nonsale3'  

# List to hold dictionaries of product non sale info
nike_products_nonsale_list = []  
count =0
# Looping through each file in the directory
for file_name in os.listdir(path):
    if file_name.endswith(".html"):
        filepath = os.path.join(path, file_name)
        with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as file:
            html_content = file.read()

        soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser')


        product_info = {}

        #  product title
        title_element = soup.select_one('h1')
        title = title_element.text.strip() if title_element else "NULL"
        print("Product title is:", title)
        product_info['title'] = title

        #  category
        category_element = soup.select_one('h2')
        category = category_element.text.strip() if category_element else "NULL"
        print("Footwear Style Category is:", category)
        product_info['category'] = category

        #  sale price
        sale_price_element = soup.find(attrs={"data-test": "product-price-reduced"})
        sale_price = sale_price_element.get_text().strip() if sale_price_element else "NULL"
        print("Product Sale Price is:", sale_price)
        product_info['sale_price'] = sale_price

        #  original price
        original_price_element = soup.find(attrs={"data-test": "product-price"})
        original_price = original_price_element.get_text().strip() if original_price_element else "NULL"
        org_price_match = re.search(r'\$\d+', original_price)
        org_price = org_price_match.group() if org_price_match else "NULL"
        print("Original Product price is:", org_price)
        product_info['original_price'] = org_price

        #  discount offer
        offer_element = soup.find(attrs={"data-testid": "OfferPercentage"})
        if offer_element:
            offer_perc = offer_element.get_text().strip()
            offer_perc_final = offer_perc.split()[-2] if offer_perc else "NULL"
            print("Discount Offer on the product is:", offer_perc_final)
        else:
            print("No discount offer available for this product.")
        product_info['discount_offer'] = offer_perc_final if offer_element else "NULL"

        # description
        desc_element = soup.select_one('.description-preview.body-2.css-1pbvugb > p')
        desc_final = desc_element.get_text(strip=True) if desc_element else "NULL"
        print("Description is:", desc_final)
        product_info['description'] = desc_final

        #  product ID
        element = soup.select_one('.description-preview__style-color.ncss-li')
        style_id = element.text.strip()[-11:] if element else "NULL"
        print("The Product ID for the product is:", style_id)
        product_info['product_id'] = style_id

        # number of reviews
        review_span = soup.select_one('h3.headline-4 > span')
        number_of_reviews = review_span.get_text(strip=True).split('(')[-1].strip(')') if review_span else "NULL"
        print("Number of reviews is:", number_of_reviews)
        product_info['number_of_reviews'] = number_of_reviews if review_span else "0"

        #  rating
        rating_div = soup.find('div', class_='css-n209rx')
        rating = rating_div.get('aria-label') if rating_div else "NULL"
        print("Rating is:", rating)
        product_info['rating'] = rating
        count+=1
        
        # Add the product_info dictionary to the list
        nike_products_nonsale_list.append(product_info)

        print("*****************************************************************************************************")

##################### CREATING TABLE FOR NON SALE SHOES ##################

import mysql.connector
import warnings

import requests
import json
import codecs
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

#ignore warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")



# Define the database and table details
SQL_DB = "nike"   um 
SQL_TABLE_NIKE = "products_nonsale"
SQL_TABLE_NIKE_DEF = "(" + \
        "product_id VARCHAR(255)," + \
        "title TEXT," + \
        "category TEXT," + \
        "sale_price VARCHAR(255)," + \
        "original_price VARCHAR(255)," + \
        "discount_offer VARCHAR(255)," + \
        "description TEXT," + \
        "number_of_reviews INT," + \
        "rating VARCHAR(255)" + \
        ")"


try:
    #connect to server
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()


    query = "CREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS " + SQL_DB
    cursor.execute(query);

    conn.database = 'nike'
    
    query = "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE
    cursor.execute(query);
        
    query = "CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS " + SQL_DB + "." + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE_DEF + ";";
    cursor.execute(query);

    
    cursor.close()
    conn.close()

    print("Created NIKE Database and Products Table")
except IOError as e:
    print(e)

    #connect to server
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()
    cursor.execute('USE nike')

    # Prepare insert query
    insert_query = f"INSERT INTO " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " (product_id, title, category, sale_price, original_price, discount_offer, description, number_of_reviews, rating) \
     VALUES (%s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s, %s);"
    
    row_count = 0
    for product in nike_products_nonsale_list:
        row_count += 1
        user_data = (
            product.get("product_id"),
            product.get("title"),
            product.get("category"),
            product.get("sale_price"),
            product.get("original_price"),
            product.get("discount_offer"),
            product.get("description"),
            product.get("number_of_reviews"),
            product.get("rating")
        )
        cursor.execute(insert_query, user_data)
        conn.commit()
        
    print(f"{row_count} rows of data inserted successfully.")
    cursor.close()
    conn.close()

except mysql.connector.Error as e:
    print("MySQL error:", e)

#creating a collections table

import mysql.connector

SQL_DB = "nike"   
SQL_TABLE_NIKE = "products_nonsale"

try:
    #connect to server
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost',
                                   user='root',
                                   password='Rach@76732',
                                   )
    cursor = conn.cursor()
    cursor.execute('USE nike')

    #  if 'collection' column already exists then nochange and add it if it doesn't alter table
    cursor.execute("SELECT * FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.COLUMNS WHERE TABLE_SCHEMA = %s AND TABLE_NAME = 'products_nonsale' AND COLUMN_NAME = 'collection'", (SQL_DB,))
    result = cursor.fetchone()
    if not result:
        query = "ALTER TABLE " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " ADD COLUMN collection VARCHAR(255)"
        cursor.execute(query);
        
     # Select all product titles from the table
    cursor.execute(f"SELECT product_id, title FROM products_nonsale;")
    products = cursor.fetchall()
        

    # Checking for Collection name in the title
        
    # first update collection with 'others'
    for product_id, title in products:
        collection_name = 'others'
        title = title.strip()  
    
    # Check if any of the known collection names are in the title, if available then update collection column
        for collection in collection_names:
            if collection.lower() in title.lower():
                collection_name = collection
                break
            
            
        update_query = f"UPDATE products_nonsale SET collection = %s WHERE product_id = %s;"
        cursor.execute(update_query, (collection_name, product_id))
        
       
    conn.commit()
    print("The 'collection' column is updated.")
except mysql.connector.Error as error:
        print("Failed to update records to nike db: ", error)

cursor.close()
conn.close()
print("MySQL connection is closed.")

    result = cursor.fetchone()

        query = "ALTER TABLE " + SQL_TABLE_NIKE + " ADD COLUMN colors INT"
        cursor.execute(query);
        
     # Select all product titles from the table
    cursor.execute(f"SELECT product_id FROM products_nonsale;")
    product_ids = cursor.fetchall()
        

    # Update the colors column for each product
    for idx, (product_id,) in enumerate(product_ids):
        if idx < len(color_numbers):  # Check to avoid index out of range
            update_query = f"UPDATE {SQL_TABLE_NIKE} SET colors = %s WHERE product_id = %s"
            cursor.execute(update_query, (color_numbers[idx], product_id))
    
    conn.commit() 
       
    
    print("The 'colors' column is updated.")
except mysql.connector.Error as error:
        print("Failed to update records to nike db: ", error)

######### DATA MODELLLING - ADDING A CATEGORIES TABLE TO THE DATABASE FROM THE SCRAPED INFORMAITON #####

import mysql.connector
from mysql.connector import Error

# Assuming 'nike_products_nonsale_list' is defined elsewhere and accessible
categories_data = [product['category'] for product in nike_products_nonsale_list]

try:
    # Connect to the MySQL database
    conn = mysql.connector.connect(host='localhost', user='root', password='your_password', database='nike')

    cursor = conn.cursor()

    # Define the category table with appropriate column(s)
    category_table_def = "category_name VARCHAR(255)"
    
    # Create the category table if it does not exist
    cursor.execute(f"CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS category ({category_table_def});")
    
    # SQL statement for inserting data
    insert_query = "INSERT INTO category (category_name) VALUES (%s);"
    
    # Inserting the categories into the category table
    for category in categories_data:
        cursor.execute(insert_query, (category,))
    
    # Make sure data is committed to the database
    conn.commit()
    
    print(f"{cursor.rowcount} rows inserted successfully into category table.")

except Error as e:
    print("Error while connecting to MySQL", e)
finally:
    # Close the cursor and the connection
    if conn.is_connected():
        cursor.close()
        conn.close()
        print("MySQL connection is closed")
